data.enText: happening or existing before the event or object that you are talking about

data.chText: 这一工作无需相关的经验。
data.enText: No previous experience is necessary for this job.

data.chText: 这辆汽车以前没换过车主。
data.enText: The car has only had one previous owner.

data.chText: 她是他与前妻生的女儿。
data.enText: She is his daughter from a previous marriage.

data.chText: 我因有约在先，无法出席。
data.enText: I was unable to attend because of a previous engagement.

data.chText: 任何前科法官都将予以考虑。
data.enText: The judge will take into consideration any previous convictions.
immediately before the time you are talking about

data.chText: 听到这消息时，我不敢相信；我就在前一天还见到过他。
data.enText: I couldn't believe it when I heard the news. I'd only seen him the previous day.

data.chText: 这座楼房早先曾用作旅馆。
data.enText: The building had previously been used as a hotel.

data.chText: 我之前曾探访过他们三天。
data.enText: I had visited them three days previously.

data.chText: 这以前，她身体一向很好。
data.enText: Previous to this, she'd always been well.

simple_means.memory_skill: pre 前 + vi 道路 + ous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 前面的路 → 以前的

ex.chText: 她前一次婚姻有一个孩子。
ex.enText: She has a child from a previous marriage.

ex.chText: 他发现他以前见过他的新同事3次。
ex.enText: He discovered that he had met his new colleague before on three previous occasions.

synonyms.bx: 指在当下所提及的事件、时间等之前发生或存在的，通常作定语。

ex.chText: 上述结论是根据以下数据得出的。
ex.enText: The foregoing conclusion is based on the following data.

synonyms.bx: 指事物在讲述、文章等中刚刚提到的，常作定语。

ex.chText: 他对和那位前总统有关的书十分感兴趣。
ex.enText: He has a great interest in books about the former president.

ex.chText: 由于经济萧条，他的收入已减少到以前的一半。
ex.enText: His income has been reduced to half its former amount due to the economic depression.

synonyms.bx: 指曾有过某种职务或地位的，也可指发生或存在于过去的。

ex.chText: 上一章的例子后面又再次被使用。
ex.enText: The examples in the preceding chapter are used again later.

ex.chText: 他们周五一起看电影的计划泡汤了，因为他们在前一天吵了一架。
ex.enText: Their plan of seeing a movie together on Friday failed because they had a quarrel on the preceding day.

synonyms.bx: 指在所提时间、地点或部分之前发生或出现的。

ex.chText: 本次讨论要求事先了解该主题的相关知识。
ex.enText: The discussion requires prior knowledge of the subject.

ex.chText: 事先未征得经理的同意不可以招收任何员工。
ex.enText: No employee can be recruited without the prior approval of the manager.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，多指先于另一事物或某一时间前存在或安排的。

value.def: A previous event or thing is one that happened or existed before the one that you are talking about.

example.ex: She has a teenage daughter from a previous marriage...
example.tran: 她前一段婚姻有一个十几岁的女儿。

value.def: You refer to the period of time or the thing immediately before the one that you are talking about as the previous one.

example.ex: It was a surprisingly dry day after the rain of the previous week...
example.tran: 上星期刚下过雨，天气却出奇地干燥。

example.ex: He recalled exactly what Bob had told him the previous night.
example.tran: 他清楚记得前一天晚上鲍勃告诉他的话。

trans: 议会中的；先决问题；停止讨论
上一页；前页；前一页；本页的上一页；上页
前代；婚龄十年以上的女性；上一代
前几年；上一年；上一年度；前年；去年
